Grinnell College is excited to host a Superfest Mini-Festival April 10th through the 13th.&#160;Superfest, held annually in San Francisco, CA since 1970 is one of the longest running disability film festivals in the world. Each year Superfest has celebrated cutting-edge cinema that portrays disability through a diverse, complex, unabashed and engaging lens.


This year, Grinnell College is bringing a Superfest to rural Iowa to showcase some of the best of recent films highlighted at Superfest. Mini-fest is co-sponsored by the Disability Cultural Center, Disability Resources, the Film Studies Department, the Office of Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion, and Drake Community Library.


&#160;

ADR is thrilled to be partnering with DCL to offer a family-friendly installment of Mini-fest.&#160;The children’s&#160;screening will feature the short film Luki and the Lights, followed by a disability-related storytime! This event is open to children of all ages + their adults. Snacks provided.&#160;


WHERE:&#160;Drake Community Library, children’s room


