“Know Your Rights” Campus Forums will be held to discuss legal protections and recourse on the most salient issues higher education and Grinnell College are facing including:&#160;FERPA (Family Education Rights and Privacy Acts),&#160;Title VI (prohibits discrimination based on race, color, national origin or shared ancestry), Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) (prohibits discrimination against individuals with disabilities in various areas of public life), Title IX (prohibits discrimination based on sex) and the Excise Tax (tax on certain college and university endowments, including Grinnell’s).&#160;


Dates for each session topic will be announced in the Campus Memo. The format of the Campus Forums will be a short presentation followed by discussion of submitted questions followed by time for question from the audience.&#160;


Please submit your question for forums throughthis qualtrics form.&#160; By having a robust set of questions and concerns in advance we can plan our time to best ensure that we are able to cover the topics of interest to the campus in each forum.&#160;

